      "kwargs": {
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "{\"success\":true,\"process_rule_id\":\"J09C\",\"process_rule\":\"1. Copy the decision table rows into table `J09C_temp` where the tour starts with `J09C`.\\n\\n2. Add column `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `J09C_temp`.\\n\\n3. Classify meter reading type in `ENTSCHEIDUNG`:\\n   - if a `HAUS` has less than 3 `EQUNR`, set `ENTSCHEIDUNG = \\\"KSA\\\"`\\n   - else set `ENTSCHEIDUNG = \\\"EVU\\\"`\\n\\n4. Join the table with `EABLG` using `INSTALLATION`.\\n\\n5. Join the result with `SALES_MASTER` and `NET_MASTER` using `EQUNR`.\\n\\n6. Compare customer data from `SALES_MASTER` and `NET_MASTER`.\\n\\n7. If sales customer data is not empty:\\n   1. Use the sales customer data table entries.\\n   Else:\\n   1. Use the net customer data table entries.\\n\\n8. Export the final table as CSV file named `J09C`. Use exactly these column names:\\n   `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`\\n\\n9. Send an email to `meter.readings@evu.com` with the CSV file attached. Use file path: `<path_to_exported_csv_file>`.\\n\\n10. Delete the temporary table.\"}",
            "id": "lc_8c44bf1f-db50-4eb1-8967-a94f425e26b5"
          }
        ],
        "type": "tool",
        "name": "retrieve_process",
        "id": "e57f9fc3-64f3-44f6-b181-3d37939bd8c2",
        "tool_call_id": "call_XtA8pxV6S7F0BpWOxrNTz99l",
        "artifact": {
          "structured_content": {
            "success": true,
            "process_rule_id": "J09C",
            "process_rule": "1. Copy the decision table rows into table `J09C_temp` where the tour starts with `J09C`.\n\n2. Add column `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `J09C_temp`.\n\n3. Classify meter reading type in `ENTSCHEIDUNG`:\n   - if a `HAUS` has less than 3 `EQUNR`, set `ENTSCHEIDUNG = \"KSA\"`\n   - else set `ENTSCHEIDUNG = \"EVU\"`\n\n4. Join the table with `EABLG` using `INSTALLATION`.\n\n5. Join the result with `SALES_MASTER` and `NET_MASTER` using `EQUNR`.\n\n6. Compare customer data from `SALES_MASTER` and `NET_MASTER`.\n\n7. If sales customer data is not empty:\n   1. Use the sales customer data table entries.\n   Else:\n   1. Use the net customer data table entries.\n\n8. Export the final table as CSV file named `J09C`. Use exactly these column names:\n   `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`\n\n9. Send an email to `meter.readings@evu.com` with the CSV file attached. Use file path: `<path_to_exported_csv_file>`.\n\n10. Delete the temporary table."
          }
        },
        "status": "success"
      }
    },
